  files/tomboy-0.3.2-1.1.x-compat.diff:
  Fix to patch to work on mono-1.0.x

*tomboy-0.3.2 (05 May 2005)

  05 May 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  +files/tomboy-0.3.2-1.1.x-compat.diff,
  +files/tomboy-0.3.2-mono-1.1.7-compat.diff, tomboy-0.3.1.ebuild,
  +tomboy-0.3.2.ebuild:
  Bump, and include some fixes for compilation with stricter mono-1.1.7

  14 Mar 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org> tomboy-0.2.2-r1.ebuild,
  -tomboy-0.2.2.ebuild, tomboy-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Mark 0.2.2-r1 stable on x86, fix deps to make sure we get 1.0.x SLOT of
  gtk-sharp, and remove on older version.

  10 Mar 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org> tomboy-0.2.2-r1.ebuild,
  tomboy-0.2.2.ebuild, tomboy-0.3.1.ebuild:
  mono moved from dev-dotnet -> dev-lang

  20 Feb 2005; David Holm <dholm@gentoo.org> tomboy-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc.

  18 Feb 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  files/tomboy-0.3.1-mono-1.1.4-compat.diff:
  Fix the 1.1.4-compat patch to work on mono-1.0.x.

*tomboy-0.3.1 (17 Feb 2005)

  17 Feb 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  +files/tomboy-0.3.1-mono-1.1.4-compat.diff, +tomboy-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Bump. Includes a few new deps, to handle gnome-panel support, as well as a
  hacky patch for mono-1.1.4 compat. See bug #79890

